      "id": "c4275cb8-92f7-4e53-a4d6-03a629a19f93",
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "- int is a primitive data type. It is raw, naked data.\r\n- Integer (with a capital I) is a Wrapper Class. It is a full-blown Object that acts like a box. Inside that box, it holds a primitive int.\r\n- When you define a class like class Node1<Integer>, Java has a strict rule: The Generic type <Integer> can ONLY be an Object. It cannot be a primitive.",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "c4275cb8-92f7-4e53-a4d6-03a629a19f93"
      }
